  substr(string, 1, 1) <- toupper(substr(string, 1, 1))
  string
}

  axis.line = element_line(colour = \black\),
  panel.border = element_blank(),
  legend.position = \top\,

```r
measurements <- read.csv("/home/engel/Documents/experiments/slam_experiment/run_table.csv")
measurements <- measurements[measurements$arena == 'point_to_point', ]
measurements$algorithm <- as.factor(measurements$algorithm)
measurements$map_resolution <- as.factor(measurements$map_resolution)
measurements$linear_update <- as.factor(measurements$linear_update)
measurements$angular_update <- as.factor(measurements$angular_update)
measurements

Data exploration

```r
measurements %>%
  group_by(algorithm, map_resolution, linear_update, angular_update) %>%
  get_summary_stats(avg_cpu, type = \full\)

measurements %>%
  group_by(algorithm) %>%
  get_summary_stats(avg_cpu, type = \full\)

# ANOVA

## Assumption checking
ANOVA has four assumptions, which are checked in this section.

### 1. Independence of samples
By the design of the experiment, samples are independent (and fully randomised).

### 2. Normality of residuals
We fit a model based on all four factors (and their interactions) as parameters.

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubW9kZWwgIDwtIGxtKGF2Z19jcHUgfiBhbGdvcml0aG0qbWFwX3Jlc29sdXRpb24qbGluZWFyX3VwZGF0ZSphbmd1bGFyX3VwZGF0ZSwgZGF0YSA9IG1lYXN1cmVtZW50cylcbnJlcyA8LSByZXNpZHVhbHMobW9kZWwpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
model  <- lm(avg_cpu ~ algorithm*map_resolution*linear_update*angular_update, data = measurements)
res <- residuals(model)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

In the plots above, some points exhibit a large distance to the reference line The normality assumption is therefore not met.

## 4. Homogeneity of variance


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxubGV2ZW5lX3Rlc3QoYXZnX2NwdSB+IGFsZ29yaXRobSptYXBfcmVzb2x1dGlvbiphbmd1bGFyX3VwZGF0ZSpsaW5lYXJfdXBkYXRlLCBkYXRhID0gbWVhc3VyZW1lbnRzKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
levene_test(avg_cpu ~ algorithm*map_resolution*angular_update*linear_update, data = measurements)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-frame-begin eyJtZXRhZGF0YSI6eyJjbGFzc2VzIjpbInRibF9kZiIsInRibCIsImRhdGEuZnJhbWUiXSwibnJvdyI6MSwibmNvbCI6NH0sInJkZiI6IlVrUllNd3BZQ2dBQUFBTUFCQUVBQUFNRkFBQUFBQVZWVkVZdE9BQUFCQUlBQUFBQkFBUUFDUUFBQUFGNEFBQURFd0FBQUFRQUFBQU5BQUFBQVFBQUFCOEFBQUFOQUFBQUFRQUFBSUFBQUFBT0FBQUFBVC9sc0xFZ0RDam9BQUFBRGdBQUFBRS83S2ZhSzJTMEtnQUFCQUlBQUFBQkFBUUFDUUFBQUFWdVlXMWxjd0FBQUJBQUFBQUVBQVFBQ1FBQUFBTmtaakVBQkFBSkFBQUFBMlJtTWdBRUFBa0FBQUFKYzNSaGRHbHpkR2xqQUFRQUNRQUFBQUZ3QUFBRUFnQUFBQUVBQkFBSkFBQUFDWEp2ZHk1dVlXMWxjd0FBQUEwQUFBQUNnQUFBQVAvLy8vOEFBQVFDQUFBQUFRQUVBQWtBQUFBRlkyeGhjM01BQUFBUUFBQUFBUUFFQUFrQUFBQUtaR0YwWVM1bWNtRnRaUUFBQVA0QUFBUUNBQUFBQVFBRUFBa0FBQUFIYjNCMGFXOXVjd0FBQWhNQUFBQUZBQUFBRUFBQUFBRUFCQUFKQUFBQUFYSUFBQUFRQUFBQUFRQUVBQWtBQUFBUGRXNXVZVzFsWkMxamFIVnVheTB4QUFBQUNnQUFBQUVBQUFBQUFBQUFEUUFBQUFFQUFBQUJBQUFBRFFBQUFBRUFBQUFFQUFBRUFnQUFBdjhBQUFBUUFBQUFCUUFFQUFrQUFBQUdaVzVuYVc1bEFBUUFDUUFBQUFWc1lXSmxiQUFFQUFrQUFBQU9jbTkzYm1GdFpYTXVjSEpwYm5RQUJBQUpBQUFBQ25KdmQzTXVkRzkwWVd3QUJBQUpBQUFBQ21OdmJITXVkRzkwWVd3QUFBRCtBQUFBL2c9PSJ9 -->

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->

The p-value is higher than 0.05, hence we fail to reject H0. Thus, we can assume homogeneity of variance  among all groups.

It is important to note that some groups have an extremely high variance (exceeding 1.5x the other variances).


<!-- rnb-text-end -->

<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuYWdnX21lYXN1cmVtZW50cyA8LSBtZWFzdXJlbWVudHMgJT4lIGdyb3VwX2J5KGFsZ29yaXRobSwgbWFwX3Jlc29sdXRpb24sIGxpbmVhcl91cGRhdGUsIGFuZ3VsYXJfdXBkYXRlKSAlPiVcbiAgZ2V0X3N1bW1hcnlfc3RhdHMoYXZnX2NwdSwgdHlwZSA9IFxcbWVhbl9zZFxcKVxuZ2dzY2F0dGVyKGFnZ19tZWFzdXJlbWVudHMsIFxcbWVhblxcLCBcXHNkXFwpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
agg_measurements <- measurements %>% group_by(algorithm, map_resolution, linear_update, angular_update) %>%
  get_summary_stats(avg_cpu, type = \mean_sd\)
ggscatter(agg_measurements, \mean\, \sd\)

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->

The assumptions for ANOVA are violated, hence we resort to PERMANOVA (using permutations).

## Running PERMANOVA

<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuc2V0LnNlZWQoMjA1MSlcbmFvdnAub3V0IDwtIGFvdnAoYXZnX2NwdSB+IGFsZ29yaXRobSptYXBfcmVzb2x1dGlvbipsaW5lYXJfdXBkYXRlKmFuZ3VsYXJfdXBkYXRlLCBkYXRhPW1lYXN1cmVtZW50cywgbWF4SXRlcj0xMDAwMDAwMDAsIG5DeWNsZT0xKVxuYGBgXG5gYGAifQ== -->

```r
```r
set.seed(2051)
aovp.out <- aovp(avg_cpu ~ algorithm*map_resolution*linear_update*angular_update, data=measurements, maxIter=100000000, nCycle=1)

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->


The results indicate a significant main effect of the algorithm, map resolution and angular update factors.

There is also a significant interaction between the algorithm ad angular update.

### Post hoc tests
Since there are only two treatments for the map resolution (high and low) we do not need to perform a post hoc test for this main effect.

To analyse the main effect of the algorithm and angular update (interaction), we first assess normality of the groups and compare their variance.


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->

shapiro_tests <- measurements %>% group_by(algorithm, angular_update)  %>% shapiro_test(avg_cpu)
shapiro_tests[order(shapiro_tests$p),]

<!-- rnb-text-begin -->

The normality of groups assumption is violated, but homogeneity of variance cannot be rejected (p > 0.05).

The assumptions for Tukey's HSB test are not met, even after transformation. Hence, we resort to the non-parametric Dunn test.


<!-- rnb-text-end -->


<!-- rnb-chunk-begin -->


<!-- rnb-source-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYGBgclxuYGBgclxuYWxnb3JpdGhtX2FuZ3VsYXJfdXBkYXRlX2ludGVyYWN0aW9uIDwtIGludGVyYWN0aW9uKG1lYXN1cmVtZW50cyRhbGdvcml0aG0sIG1lYXN1cmVtZW50cyRhbmd1bGFyX3VwZGF0ZSlcbkR1bm5UZXN0KGF2Z19jcHUgfiBhbGdvcml0aG1fYW5ndWxhcl91cGRhdGVfaW50ZXJhY3Rpb24sIG1lYXN1cmVtZW50cywgbWV0aG9kPSdCSCcpXG5gYGBcbmBgYCJ9 -->

```r
```r
algorithm_angular_update_interaction <- interaction(measurements$algorithm, measurements$angular_update)
DunnTest(avg_cpu ~ algorithm_angular_update_interaction, measurements, method='BH')

<!-- rnb-source-end -->
